cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new probabilistic model for recommendation systems that utilizes a Poisson process and time-sensitive factorization models. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper focuses on recommendation systems and how to model implicit feedback data to make personalized recommendations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): One of the variants of the proposed framework (SRPF) models the social aspect of product adoption, which falls under this sub-category. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science): The paper's focus on modeling user behavior and social aspects of product adoption also falls under this sub-category. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper develops a variational algorithm for approximate posterior inference that scales up to massive data sets, which falls under this sub-category.
